31142063429388box: 9, media: ID: 426.0533 (Material Type: moving images)

Extent

1 media elements VHS

Physical Characteristics and Technical Requirements

Color, sound

Duration: 60 minutes

Original format: VHS

Series II: Gay USA Collection misc material, April 1980 - October 2006, undated

Extent

.1 Linear Feet In 2 folders
1 videocassettes (u-matic)
1 videocassettes (minidv)

Scope and Content

This series contains two folders of paper material from the Gay USA collection, plus two commercial media items: a mini-DV head cleaning tape, and a U-matic copy of Frankie Goes to Hollywood's 'Relax' music video.

Paper material, January 2005 - October 2006, undated

31142063429339box: 4, folder: 1 (Material Type: Mixed Materials)

Scope and Contents

This folder contains four sheets of paper. The first is one page of hand written notes , the second is titled "The Earliest Gay Pickets: When, Where, Why" and lists 11 pickets for LGBT causes, the third and four pages are a liscencing agreement between Ann Northrop and WHYY-TV Philadelphia for the use of the film "Gay Pioneers" in the Gay U.S.A. program.

Paper material, 1980-1996, undated

31142063429339box: 4, folder: 2 (Material Type: Mixed Materials)

Scope and Contents

The folder contains a GCN business card for Gay USA director Louis Maletta, an article ripped out of HX Magazine about Gay Cable Network (written by David Cohen, August 1996), and a letter from a devout Christian that includes a pamphlet called 'The Sissy.'

Misc. commercial media

31142063429339box: 4 (Material Type: videos)

Extent

1 videocassettes (u-matic)
1 videocassettes (minidv)

Scope and Contents

This file contains two pieces of commercial media related to Gay USA production material from 2000-2001: one Umatic tape of the music video 'Relax' by the band Frankie Goes to Hollywood, and another a miniDV player head cleaning tape.
